data.content:
`[ExpectedException]` was removed in MSTest v4. Replace it with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()` inside the test body.

Here's the fix for your two test methods:

```csharp
// Before (v3)
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After (v4)
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

Same pattern for `Process_InvalidState_ThrowsInvalidOperation` — wrap the throwing call in `Assert.ThrowsExactly<InvalidOperationException>(() => ...)`.

For **async** methods, use `await Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<T>(...)` instead.

